# Phase 5 — Naming Cleanup & Frameworks Boundary

## The Problem

Rho accumulated multiple names for the same concepts. Config files used `mounts:`
while the code used `plugins:`. Comments said "reasoner" while the module was
`TurnStrategy`. The tape projection behaviour was `Rho.Tape.Context` even though
"context" collided with `Rho.Context` (the ambient state struct). And
`rho_frameworks` depended on `rho_cli` for a single config lookup call.

This naming confusion imposes a tax on every reader: which name is canonical?
Are `Mount` and `Plugin` different things? (No.) Is `reasoner` deprecated? (Yes,
but it's still in comments and one config key.)

## What Phase 5 Does

Two independent sub-tasks: **5A** kills naming aliases, **5B** cuts a spurious
dependency.

---

## 5A: Naming Cleanup

### Tape.Context -> Tape.Projection

The behaviour that turns a durable tape into LLM message history was called
`Rho.Tape.Context` with its default implementation `Rho.Tape.Context.Tape`.
Both names are confusing:

- "Context" collides with `Rho.Context`, the ambient state struct
- "Tape" as both the behaviour name and the implementation name
  (`Tape.Context.Tape`) is circular

**After:**

| Before | After |
|--------|-------|
| `Rho.Tape.Context` | `Rho.Tape.Projection` |
| `Rho.Tape.Context.Tape` | `Rho.Tape.Projection.JSONL` |

The new name `Projection` describes what the module does: it projects
(transforms) a tape into a form the LLM can consume. The implementation name
`JSONL` describes the storage format.

Backward-compatible delegator modules remain at the old paths so that any
external code using `Rho.Tape.Context` or `Rho.Tape.Context.Tape` continues
to work.

**Files changed:**

```
# New files (canonical)
apps/rho/lib/rho/tape/projection.ex          — behaviour
apps/rho/lib/rho/tape/projection/jsonl.ex     — default implementation

# Old files (backward-compatible delegators)
apps/rho/lib/rho/tape/context.ex              — delegates build/1
apps/rho/lib/rho/tape/context/tape.ex         — delegates all callbacks

# Updated references (~15 files)
config/config.exs                             — tape_module config
apps/rho/config/config.exs                    — tape_module config
apps/rho/lib/rho/config.ex                    — default fallback
apps/rho/lib/rho/run_spec.ex                  — @defaults
apps/rho/lib/rho/runner.ex                    — 3 references
apps/rho/lib/rho/agent_loop/tape.ex           — struct default + moduledoc
apps/rho/lib/rho/agent_loop/recorder.ex       — rebuild_context/1
apps/rho/lib/rho/context.ex                   — comment
apps/rho/lib/rho/agent/worker.ex              — memory_mod fallback
apps/rho_stdlib/lib/rho/stdlib/plugins/multi_agent.ex — memory_mod fallback
apps/rho_stdlib/lib/rho/stdlib/plugins/tape.ex        — moduledoc
apps/rho/test/support/turn_strategy_harness.ex         — test fixture
apps/rho/test/rho/turn_strategy/typed_structured_test.exs — test fixture
```

### Config Keys: mounts -> plugins, reasoner -> turn_strategy

The `.rho.exs` config file used `mounts:` (9 agent definitions) and
`reasoner:` (4 agents). These are legacy names from before the Plugin/
TurnStrategy rename.

**After:** All occurrences updated to `plugins:` and `turn_strategy:`.

`Rho.CLI.Config.normalize_keys/1` still handles the old keys for backward
compatibility, but now emits `IO.warn` deprecation warnings when they're
encountered.

### Stale Comment Cleanup

| Location | Before | After |
|----------|--------|-------|
| `recorder.ex` | "Structured reasoner" / "Direct reasoner" | "TypedStructured strategy" / "Direct strategy" |
| `plugin.ex` moduledoc | References `Rho.Mount` legacy alias | Removed, describes behaviour directly |
| `runtime.ex` moduledoc | "the reasoner" | "the turn strategy" |
| `runner.ex` opts doc | `reasoner (alias)` | "legacy alias" |
| `worker.ex` | `reasoner: config.turn_strategy` | `turn_strategy: config.turn_strategy` |
| Plugin moduledocs | "Mount providing..." | "Plugin providing..." |

---

## 5B: Frameworks Boundary

### The Dependency

`rho_frameworks` declared a dependency on `:rho_cli`:

```elixir
# apps/rho_frameworks/mix.exs (before)
defp deps do
  [
    {:rho, in_umbrella: true},
    {:rho_stdlib, in_umbrella: true},
    {:rho_cli, in_umbrella: true},    # <-- unnecessary
    ...
  ]
end
```

The only usage was a single call in the hiring demo:

```elixir
# apps/rho_frameworks/lib/rho_frameworks/demos/hiring/simulation.ex:93
config = Rho.CLI.Config.agent(role)
```

### The Fix

`Rho.Config.agent_config/1` (in `apps/rho/lib/rho/config.ex`) already
discovers `Rho.CLI.Config` at runtime via `Code.ensure_loaded?/1`. It
returns the same config map with a fallback when CLI is not loaded.

```elixir
# After — uses the core module's runtime discovery
config = Rho.Config.agent_config(role)
```

`:rho_cli` removed from `rho_frameworks/mix.exs` deps. The dependency
graph is now:

```
rho_frameworks -> rho, rho_stdlib     (no more rho_cli)
rho_web        -> rho, rho_stdlib, rho_cli, rho_frameworks
rho_cli        -> rho, rho_stdlib
rho_stdlib     -> rho
```

## Verification

All checks pass after both sub-tasks:

- `mix compile --warnings-as-errors` — clean
- `mix rho.smoke` — 4 tests, 0 failures
- `mix rho.verify` — 12 tests, 0 failures
- `mix test apps/rho/test/` — 303 tests, 0 failures
